questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot service running on Tomcat experiences progressive performance degradation, culminating in a `java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: GC overhead limit exceeded`. The application processes batches of data using a thread pool. A senior developer suspects a leak associated with transaction boundaries. Below is the suspect code snippet:

java
@Service
public class OrderProcessingService {
    private final ThreadLocal<List<OrderContext>> contextHolder = ThreadLocal.withInitial(ArrayList::new);

    @Transactional
    public void processBatch(List<Order> orders) {
        for (Order order : orders) {
            contextHolder.get().add(new OrderContext(order));
            enrichAndValidate(order);
        }
        saveBatch();
    }

    @Transactional
    public void saveBatch() {
        List<OrderContext> contexts = contextHolder.get();
        // Write to database...
        contexts.clear();
    }
}
